  "body": "`kube-scheduler` doesn't have the ability to start an https server. This means that it can't have any authentication and authorization protecting debug and metrics and it can't be exposed anywhere but localhost. Unfortunately, the default at the moment is 0.0.0.0, so we have a bad combination of defaults even.\r\n\r\n@kubernetes/sig-scheduling-misc \r\n\r\n@aveshagarwal @sttts once we figure out how we're going to wire https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/58982 we should apply a congruent solution here",
